# ЁЯз▒ Phase-0: Requirement & Compliance Understanding (рж╕ржмржЪрзЗрзЯрзЗ ржЧрзБрж░рзБрждрзНржмржкрзВрж░рзНржг)

### Pharmacy-specific ржмрж╛рж╕рзНрждржм ржЪрж╛рж╣рж┐ржжрж╛
* Batch number tracking
* Expiry date mandatory
* Controlled drugs (restricted access)
* Stock accuracy (no negative stock)
* Audit trail (ржХрзЗ ржХржЦржи ржХрзА ржХрж░рж▓рзЛ)

ЁЯСЙ ржПржЦрж╛ржирзЗ ржнрзБрж▓ ржХрж░рж▓рзЗ ржкрзБрж░рзЛ system fail

# ЁЯЯв Phase-1: Core Foundation (Week 1)

## Tech Stack (Recommended)
* ASP.NET Core Web API (.NET 8/9)
* EF Core + MySQL
* JWT Authentication
* Role-based Authorization

## User Roles (Very Important)

| Role          | Access                 |
| | |
| Admin         | Full access            |
| Pharmacist    | Sell, view stock       |
| Store Manager | Purchase, stock update |
| Auditor       | Read-only              |

ЁЯСЙ Role ржнрзБрж▓ рж╣рж▓рзЗ legal problem рж╣рждрзЗ ржкрж╛рж░рзЗ

# ЁЯЯв Phase-2: Database Design (Healthcare-grade)

## Medicine Table
```
MedicineId
Name
GenericName
Manufacturer
Category
IsControlled (bool)
```

## Stock Table (Batch-based)
```
MedicineStock-
Id
MedicineId (FK)
BatchNumber
ExpiryDate
PurchasePrice
SellingPrice
Quantity
```

ЁЯСЙ Batch + Expiry ржЫрж╛рзЬрж╛ pharmacy system INVALID

## Supplier Table
```
SupplierId
Name
LicenseNumber
Contact
```

## Audit Log Table (Mandatory)
```
AuditLogId
UserId
Action
EntityName
OldValue
NewValue
Timestamp
```

# ЁЯЯв Phase-3: Authentication & Security (Week 2)

## Security Rules
* JWT + Refresh Token
* Password hashing
* HTTPS only
* Role-based API access

### Example

* Pharmacist тЭМ cannot edit purchase price
* Auditor тЭМ cannot update stock

ЁЯСЙ Security = core feature, not add-on

# ЁЯЯв Phase-4: Inventory Operations (Week 3)

## Add Medicine Stock
* Mandatory batch number
* Mandatory expiry date
* Quantity validation
* Supplier validation

## Stock Update Rules
* Quantity never negative
* Expired stock cannot be sold
* Controlled medicine needs permission

## Real-World Rule
> Same medicine, different batch = different stock

# ЁЯЯв Phase-5: Sales & Dispensing Logic (Week 4)

## Sell Medicine Flow
1. Search medicine
2. System auto-selects earliest expiry batch
3. Check stock & expiry
4. Deduct quantity
5. Log transaction

### Critical Validation

* Expired medicine тЭМ
* Insufficient stock тЭМ
* Unauthorized user тЭМ

ЁЯСЙ This logic saves lives

# ЁЯЯв Phase-6: Expiry & Alert System (Week 5)

## Expiry Monitoring
* 30 days before expiry тЖТ warning
* Expired тЖТ auto block sale

## Alerts
* Low stock alert
* Expiry alert
* Controlled drug alert

ЁЯСЙ Background job (async)

# ЁЯЯв Phase-7: Purchase & Supplier Management (Week 6)

## Purchase Flow
* Create purchase order
* Receive stock
* Validate invoice
* Update stock batch-wise

## CSV Bulk Import
* 10k+ medicine import
* Chunk processing
* Transaction safety

# ЁЯЯв Phase-8: Reporting & Audit (Week 7)

## Mandatory Reports
* Daily sales
* Expired medicine
* Low stock
* Purchase vs sales
* Controlled drug report

ЁЯСЙ Auditor role = read-only

# ЁЯЯв Phase-9: Performance & Reliability (Week 8)

## Performance
* Pagination everywhere
* `AsNoTracking()` for reports
* Caching read-only data

## Reliability
* Transaction usage
* Retry policy
* Global exception handling

# ЁЯЯв Phase-10: Online & Production Ready (Week 9)

## Deployment
* Docker container
* Cloud hosting (Azure / AWS)
* Secure file storage
* Backup strategy

## Monitoring
* Logging (Serilog)
* Health checks
* Error alert










